Implemented Vercel Speed Insights for Next.js Project

## Summary
Successfully installed and configured Vercel Speed Insights for the school-erp-platform frontend. The implementation follows the latest official Vercel documentation guidelines for Next.js 14.

## Changes Made

### 1. Package Installation
- Added `@vercel/speed-insights` (v2.0.0) to dependencies
- Updated package-lock.json with the new dependency tree

### 2. Code Changes
Modified: `frontend/src/app/layout.tsx`
- Added import: `import { SpeedInsights } from "@vercel/speed-insights/next";`
- Added `<SpeedInsights />` component inside the `<body>` tag, after the `<AppProviders>` component

## Implementation Details

Following the official Vercel Speed Insights quickstart guide (https://vercel.com/docs/speed-insights/quickstart), the implementation uses the framework-specific Next.js integration for version 14.2.28:

1. **Package Manager**: Used npm (detected from existing package-lock.json)
2. **Integration Type**: Next.js App Router (v13.5+) - using the `@vercel/speed-insights/next` export
3. **Placement**: Added to the root layout file as recommended for App Router projects

## Verification

✅ Build completed successfully with no errors
✅ Linter passed with no new warnings or errors
✅ All existing functionality preserved
✅ Lock file updated correctly

## Next Steps

To enable Speed Insights data collection on Vercel:
1. Deploy the application to Vercel
2. Enable "Speed Insights" in the Vercel dashboard for the project
3. Data will appear in the dashboard after users visit the site

## Files Modified

- `frontend/package.json` - Added @vercel/speed-insights dependency
- `frontend/package-lock.json` - Updated dependency lock file
- `frontend/src/app/layout.tsx` - Integrated SpeedInsights component

## Notes

- The SpeedInsights component is lightweight and only collects performance metrics when enabled in the Vercel dashboard
- No configuration changes are required for basic functionality
- The component automatically tracks Core Web Vitals and other performance metrics
- Implementation follows best practices for Next.js App Router projects with RTL (right-to-left) support
